library(tidyverse)

library(dplyr)
library(ggridges)
library(GGally)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'GGally':
##   method from   
##   +.gg   ggplot2
library(patchwork)
library(forcats)

coffee <- coffee_ratings %>%
  mutate(country_of_origin=fct_recode(country_of_origin,"Hawai‘i" = "United States (Hawaii)","Tanzania"="Tanzania, United Republic Of"))
data <- coffee%>%
  group_by(country_of_origin)%>%
  count()%>%
  filter(n>30)%>%
  left_join(coffee)
## Joining, by = "country_of_origin"
order_to <- data %>%
  group_by(country_of_origin) %>%
  summarize(mean(acidity)) %>%
  arrange(desc(`mean(acidity)`)) %>%
  pull(country_of_origin)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
data$country_of_origin <- factor(data$country_of_origin,levels = order_to)
ggplot(data, aes(x=acidity,y=country_of_origin,fill=country_of_origin)) +
  ggridges::geom_density_ridges(scale = 0.95) 
## Picking joint bandwidth of 0.0936

ggplot(data, aes(x=country_of_origin, y=acidity))+
  geom_boxplot()

data1<-data%>%
  group_by(country_of_origin)%>%
  summarise(med=median(acidity))%>%
  left_join(data)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
## Joining, by = "country_of_origin"
data_sorted <- data1%>%
  mutate(country_of_origin = fct_reorder(country_of_origin, med))%>%
  filter(acidity > 6)
library(showtext)
## Loading required package: sysfonts
## Loading required package: showtextdb
library(ggsci)
font_add_google("Poppins", "Poppins")
font_add_google("Roboto Mono", "Roboto Mono")
showtext_auto()

#theme_set(theme_light(base_size = 8, base_family = "Poppins"))

ggplot(data_sorted, aes(x=country_of_origin, y= acidity))+
  #geom_point(size=1, alpha=0.2)+
  geom_violin(color="chocolate4", fill="darkgoldenrod", alpha =0.5)+
  coord_flip() +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(5, 9),expand = c(0.005, 0.005))+
  theme(legend.position = "none", axis.title.x = element_text(color = "black", size = 10, vjust = -0.35), axis.title.y = element_text(color= "black", size = 10, vjust =0.35), panel.background = element_rect(size=1, fill= "bisque2"), plot.background = element_rect( fill = "bisque2"),axis.text.x = element_text(color="black"), axis.text.y = element_text(color="black"), panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(x="Country of Origin", y = "Acidity Rating")
